e underlying distribution changes.\n\n## Update on Subsequent Build Attempts\n\nAfter my commit analysis, the system attempted several fixes:\n\n1. **Attempt 4**: Added `autoconf` package to Dockerfile and set `base_os_version: ubuntu-24-04` in project.yaml\n   - Result: Failed - Ubuntu repositories only provide autoconf 2.69, not 2.71+\n\n2. **Attempt 5**: Patched libtiff\'s `configure.ac` to accept autoconf 2.69 instead of 2.71+\n   - Result: **SUCCESS** for the autoconf issue! The build progressed to compilation stage\n   - New error: Compilation error in `vipspng.c` - missing `#include <errno.h>`\n\nThe commit analysis was crucial in identifying the root cause, and the subsequent fix (patching libtiff) successfully resolved the autoconf version issue, allowing the build to progress to the next stage.'}
